Even at that the country is yet to find out how to manage its ecology. This state of affairs has resulted to resource conflicts annually in the Northcentral and North Eastern parts of Nigeria.

In addition to ecological related conflicts, warfare and bomb explosions have taken paramount position in the State. Since 2013 almost all the Zones in the North had being in one way or another bombarded by explosions emanating from Boko Haram. The war in the north has of recent spread to the south. What is originally an internal conflict within the locality of some house hold or Tribe has metamorphose into an international crisis that directly or otherwise have close proximity with a lot of homes. It is a poke in the eyes of those who felt that Africans are beasts who never share their pain with others. All efforts to bring this unpleasant situation to a halt is proving abortive.

Our Chief Missionary has seen it all and not found wanting. He has in a very discreet ways but for the benefit of all protected the church from these storms and has given her the needed Leap and Moment to make herself distant with the people disasters.
